Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 1
HTTP Server Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click on "Data-Sender" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "HTTP Server".
4
You can select a "read only" IoT Gateway (top section), whose tags have read-only
permissions, or a "read and write" IoT Gateway (bottom section), whose tags have
read and write permissions. You can open the list of enabled Gateways by clicking
on the drop down menu of the required section.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
The gateway lists contain ONLY gateways that are already enabled.
5
Click the "Add" button to the right of the "IoT Gateway for HTTP Server" field to
add the selected IoT Gateway to the table below.
6
You can click on the "pencil" icon to edit an already exposed Gateway.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Edit the name and click on the "Save" button to apply the change.
8
Above each table, there is a "+" button that adds a new row to the corresponding
table and a "Export Table Data" button that exports the table's data to a file
("generated.csv").
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Move to "Manage Iot Gateways" to view the list of Kepware's IoT Gateways for
HTTP Server. In this section you can enable/disable Kepware's IoT Gateways in
"read-only" or "read and write" permissions mode.
10
Enable/Disable each IoT Gateway for HTTP Server by selecting the checkbox on
the right.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Move to "Host".
12
Select the host to which you want to bind the HTTP server from the drop down
menu: "127.0.0.1" (localhost only) or 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces).
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Move to "Port".
14
Select the "HTTP Server Port" checkbox if you want to use a custom port, instead
of the default (8080).
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
15
Enter the custom port number in the new "Custom Port" field.
16
Move to "Security".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
17
You can Enable/Disable the "Transport Layer Security" (TLS) using the
corresponding checkbox.
18
You can also Enable/Disable the "HTTP Server authentication" using the
corresponding checkbox.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
19
If the authentication is enabled, you can set/change the HTTP Server
authentication's credentials within the "HTTP Server Username" and "HTTP Server
Password" fields.
20
You can now click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 11
21
Select the "HTTP service status" to disable the Thingworx service. After this
operation you will be directed to the "Data Sender" page.
22
Select the "HTTP Server disabled" checkbox to enable HTTP service again.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 12
23
You can now return to the Thingworx page.
24
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 13
25
Select the required option from "HTTP service commands" to start, stop or restart
the HTTP service.
26
Select the "Reboot Data Sender" checkbox to reboot the Data Sender. Click the
"Apply" button to start the reboot.
